<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,387,738]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,392,459,485]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Natural history.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carlgren" authorityYear="1951" box="[401,700,459,485]" class="Anthozoa" family="Actiniidae" genus="Bunodosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="californicum">
<emphasis box="[401,700,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Bunodosoma californicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the intertidal zone, attached to rocks, in tide pools and crevices, in protected sites (
<bibRefCitation author="Daly, M." box="[461,596,495,521]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="377 - 390" refId="ref12886" refString="Daly, M. (2004 a) Anatomy and Taxonomy of three species of sea anemones (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Actiniidae) from the Gulf of California, including Isoaulactinia hespervolita Daly, n. sp. Pacific Science, 3, 377 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.1353 / psc. 2004.0030" type="journal article" year="2004">Daly 2004a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barragan, Y. &amp; Sanchez, C. &amp; Rodriguez, E." box="[608,841,495,522]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="501 - 549" refId="ref12499" refString="Barragan, Y., Sanchez, C. &amp; Rodriguez, E. (2019) First inventory of sea anemones (Cnidaria: Actiniaria) from La Paz Bay, southern Gulf of California (Mexico). Zootaxa, 4559 (3), 501 - 549. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4559.3.4" type="journal article" year="2019">
Barragán 
<emphasis box="[717,766,495,521]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="168" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,387,738]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,531,557]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species has been reported in Mexico, 
<collectingCountry box="[853,987,531,557]" name="El Salvador" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">El Salvador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1045,1173,531,557]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. In Mexico is found in Cabo Pulmo, Puerto Escondido, Cerritos, Espíritu Santo Island, Tecolote, Punta Coyote and Balandra, along the coast of Baja California Sur; in Los Angeles Bay, in the coast of Baja California; and in Puerto Peñasco and Tiburon Island, in the coast of Sonora (
<bibRefCitation author="Carlgren, O." box="[543,710,639,665]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 121" refId="ref12795" refString="Carlgren, O. (1949) A survey of the Ptychodactiaria, Corallimorpharia and Actiniaria (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). Kunglia Svenska Vetenskaps Akademiens Handlingar, 1, 1 - 121." type="journal article" year="1949">Carlgren 1949</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carlgren, O." box="[722,781,639,666]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="415 - 449" refId="ref12829" refString="Carlgren, O. (1951) The actinian fauna of the Gulf of California. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 101, 415 - 449." type="journal article" year="1951">1951</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Daly, M." box="[794,928,639,665]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="377 - 390" refId="ref12886" refString="Daly, M. (2004 a) Anatomy and Taxonomy of three species of sea anemones (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Actiniidae) from the Gulf of California, including Isoaulactinia hespervolita Daly, n. sp. Pacific Science, 3, 377 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.1353 / psc. 2004.0030" type="journal article" year="2004">Daly 2004a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hendrickx, M. E. &amp; Brusca, R. C. &amp; Findley, L. T." box="[940,1190,639,666]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" refId="ref15097" refString="Hendrickx, M. E., Brusca, R. C. &amp; Findley, L. T. (2005) Listado y Distribucion de la Macrofauna del Golfo de California, Mexico. Parte 1. Invertebrados. Arizona-Sonora Desert Museum, Tucson, Arizona, 429 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Hendrickx 
<emphasis box="[1067,1117,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al</emphasis>
. 2005
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Quesada, A. J. &amp; Acuna, F. H. &amp; Cortes, J." box="[1203,1431,639,666]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref16010" refString="Quesada, A. J., Acuna, F. H. &amp; Cortes, J. (2015) First record of the sea anemone Bunodosoma californicum (Cnidaria: Actiniaria) on the Pacific coast of Costa Rica. Marine Biodiversity Records, 8, 1 - 3. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 1755267215000536" type="journal article" year="2015">
Quesada 
<emphasis box="[1308,1358,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barragan, Y. &amp; Sanchez, C. &amp; Rodriguez, E." box="[151,386,675,702]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="501 - 549" refId="ref12499" refString="Barragan, Y., Sanchez, C. &amp; Rodriguez, E. (2019) First inventory of sea anemones (Cnidaria: Actiniaria) from La Paz Bay, southern Gulf of California (Mexico). Zootaxa, 4559 (3), 501 - 549. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4559.3.4" type="journal article" year="2019">
Barragán 
<emphasis box="[261,311,675,701]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record for Playa Esmeralda, in Baja California; and in Punta Eugenia, Bahía Asunción, Punta Abreojos and San Juanico, in Baja California Sur.
</paragraph>
